    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Natural satellites that orbit relatively close to their parent planet on a prograde, uninclined circular orbit. Regular satellites are believed to have been formed out of the same collapsing region of the protoplanetary disk that created its primary planet.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
